IC50_Qualifier: This qualifier is to be used with the next TID, IC50. If the qualifier is =, the IC50 result equals the value in that column. If the qualifier is >, the IC50 result is greater than that value. If the qualifier is <, the IC50 result is smaller than that value
IC50: IC50 value determined using a sigmoidal dose response equation
Std.Err(IC50): Standard Error of the IC50 value
nH: Hill coefficient determined using sigmoidal dose response equation
Excluded_Points_first_point: Flags to indicate which of the first dose-response points were excluded from analysis. (1) means the titration point was excluded and (0) means the point was not excluded.
Excluded_Points_second_point: Flags to indicate which of the second dose-response points were excluded from analysis. (1) means the titration point was excluded and (0) means the point was not excluded.
